<DocsLayout title="Getting Started - Infinity Metrics">
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>

  <p>
    Welcome to Infinity Metrics! This guide will walk you through setting up
    your first analytics site, integrating the tracking script, and
    understanding your analytics dashboard.
  </p>

  <div class="note">
    <h4>üìã Prerequisites</h4>
    <p>
      Make sure you have <strong>Infinity Metrics installed</strong> on your server.
      If you haven't done this yet, start with our <a href="/docs/installation"
        >Installation guide</a
      >.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Step 1: Access Your Dashboard</h2>

  <p>Once Infinity Metrics is running, access your dashboard:</p>

  <div class="command">curl http://your-server:8080</div>

  <p>
    Open your browser and navigate to your server's URL to see the Infinity
    Metrics dashboard.
  </p>

  <h2>Step 2: Create Your First Site</h2>

  <p>After logging in, you'll be prompted to create your first site:</p>

  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>Site Name:</strong> Enter a descriptive name (e.g., "My Website")
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Domain:</strong> Enter your website's domain (e.g., "example.com")
    </li>
    <li><strong>Timezone:</strong> Select your preferred timezone</li>
    <li>
      <strong>Public Stats:</strong> Choose whether to make stats publicly viewable
    </li>
  </ol>

  <div class="success">
    <h4>‚úÖ Site Created!</h4>
    <p>
      Your site has been created successfully. You'll receive a unique <strong
        >Site ID</strong
      > that you'll need for the next step.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Step 3: Install the Tracking Script</h2>

  <p>
    Add the Infinity Metrics tracking script to your website's head section:
  </p>

  <pre><code class="language-html">&lt;script src="https://your-server:8080/infinity.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  Infinity.init(&#123;
    site_id: 'your-site-id',
    api_host: 'https://your-server:8080'
  &#125;);
&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>

  <h2>Step 4: Verify Tracking</h2>

  <p>To verify that tracking is working correctly:</p>

  <ol>
    <li>Visit your website in a new browser tab</li>
    <li>Navigate to your Infinity Metrics dashboard</li>
    <li>Look for the "Real-time" section</li>
    <li>You should see your visit appear within 30 seconds</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Step 5: Understanding Your Dashboard</h2>

  <p>Your Infinity Metrics dashboard provides comprehensive analytics:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Unique Visitors:</strong> Number of individual people who visited
    </li>
    <li><strong>Page Views:</strong> Total number of pages viewed</li>
    <li><strong>Bounce Rate:</strong> Percentage of single-page sessions</li>
    <li><strong>Session Duration:</strong> Average time spent on your site</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Custom Events</h2>

  <p>Track custom events to understand user behavior:</p>

  <pre><code class="language-javascript">// Track a custom event
Infinity.track('signup', &#123;
  plan: 'premium',
  source: 'landing_page'
&#125;);

// Track revenue
Infinity.track('purchase', &#123;
  revenue: 29.99,
  currency: 'USD',
  product: 'premium_plan'
&#125;);</code></pre>

  <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

  <div class="warning">
    <h4>‚ö†Ô∏è Common Issues</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>No data appearing:</strong> Check that the site_id is correct and
        the script is loading
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>CORS errors:</strong> Ensure your domain is added to the allowed
        origins
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Blocked by ad blockers:</strong> Consider using a custom domain for
        tracking
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

